text: Download the installer from python.org, run it, and make sure to check the option to add Python to PATH.
pip is included with Python by default. You can update it using: python -m pip install --upgrade pip.
Use python -m venv venv to create a virtual environment, then activate it using the activation script.
A Python list is a mutable, ordered collection that can store elements of different types.
Download the JetBrains Toolbox from jetbrains.com and install IntelliJ IDEA through the toolbox.
Use git clone followed by the repository URL in your terminal.
Git is a version control system used to track changes in code and collaborate with others.
First stage changes using git add, then create a commit using git commit -m.
A Python dictionary is a key-value data structure that allows fast lookup by key.
Use pip install followed by the package name in your terminal.
A virtual environment isolates Python dependencies for a specific project.
Navigate to the script directory and run python script_name.py in the terminal.
A Python tuple is an immutable ordered collection of elements.
Use pip install --upgrade followed by the package name.
GitHub is a platform for hosting Git repositories and collaborating on software projects.
Use git branch to create a new branch and git checkout to switch to it.
An IDE is an Integrated Development Environment that provides tools for writing and debugging code.
Download Visual Studio Code from code.visualstudio.com and follow the installer instructions.
A Python function is a reusable block of code defined using the def keyword.
Use the class keyword followed by the class name and define methods inside it.
